<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
Title<strong> : HOW ARE YOU INTELLIGENT?</strong></p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
<strong>Abstract:</strong></p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;<br>
</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
Someone may know the exact answer to a complex mathematical word problem. B=
ut if asked to write down the steps in the right sequence, will blank out/g=
o blank..</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
Some need soft music playing while studying , while others may need pin dro=
p silence.</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
Some read aloud to remember and study, while another may just need to read =
through silently.</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
Some are not able to spatially visualize and place things abstractly in rel=
ation to other things, while an architect is able to visualize complex plac=
ements in complex settings.</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
Some others may be able to repeat exactly what they saw in a well enacted p=
lay on any subject, be able to discuss intricacies of the issue, but not be=
 able to comprehend if he read exactly the same in a script.</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
If a cluttered desk is a sign of a cluttered mind, of what, then, is an emp=
ty desk a sign?=E2=80=94who said this?...... EINSTEIN&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;<br>
</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
It is not about how intelligent you are but about how you are intelligent.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;Dyslexic children are usually strong in all intelligences other than =
mathematical logic and linguistic</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
 background-color:rgb(255,255,255)">
<strong>But how do we understand Dyslexia is only a difference rather than =
a deficit?</strong><br>
</p>
<p style=3D"font-family:Calibri,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:16px;=
